==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Paramastoid
<hw>Par`a*mas"toid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>para-</ets> + <ets>mastoid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Situated beside, or near, the mastoid portion of the temporal bone;
paroccipital; -- applied especially to a process of the skull in some
animals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Paramatta</ent>⟦br⟧
